"script": "A starfish doesn't bite its food, it eats it from the outside in. When it finds a clam, it crawls on top and grips the shell with hundreds of tiny suction feet. Then it slowly pries the shell open, just a sliver, no wider than a hair. And here's the disturbing part. The starfish pushes its own stomach out through its mouth, sliding it into that tiny gap. Once inside, the stomach digests the clam alive, turning it to soup. Finally, the starfish sucks its stomach back in, its meal already finished.",
